The cost of the first glass is $5. 

For the remaining 15 glasses, the discount is 60%, which means Kailar will pay only 40% of the original price for each glass.

Therefore, Kailar needs to pay $35 for the 16 glasses. 

The answer is $35.

Eliza earns $10 per hour for the first 40 hours she works each week. After that, she earns 1.2 times the regular hourly rate for any overtime hours. This week, Eliza worked 45 hours. 

For the first 40 hours, she earns $10 per hour. So, for the first 40 hours, she earns 40 * $10 = $400.

For the remaining 5 hours, she earns 1.2 times the regular hourly rate. So, for the overtime hours, she earns 5 * ($10 * 1.2) = $60.

Therefore, Eliza earns a total of $400 + $60 = $460 this week.

The answer is $460.

The answer is $92.
